The White House Press Secretary, Jay Carney, held a press briefing on September 18, 2013. He announced that President Obama would be attending a memorial service for the victims of the shooting at the Washington Navy Yard. Carney discussed the possibility of a government shutdown, stating that House Republicans were pursuing a path away from compromise and towards a shutdown. He emphasized the importance of funding the government and avoiding unnecessary harm to the economy. Carney also addressed the issue of the debt ceiling, stating that the President would not negotiate over Congress's responsibility to pay its bills. He discussed the President's efforts to find common ground with Republicans on budget policy and the need for Congress to act responsibly. Carney also mentioned the President's letter to Iran's President Rouhani and the potential for diplomatic resolution of the nuclear issue. He stated that there were no plans for a meeting between the two leaders at the United Nations General Assembly. Carney also discussed the President's position on immigration reform and the need for comprehensive legislation. Finally, he mentioned that the President had no plans to use executive authority to delay deportations of illegal immigrants.